# Search System

Search is the discovery engine of LexMastery.

It is not just a query tool.

It is a learning navigation system.

---

# Product Vision

Search must:

- help users find any learning resource instantly
- understand semantic intent
- connect across all modules
- improve learning discovery
- reduce friction in navigation

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

SearchController (Riverpod)

↓

SearchState

↓

SearchRepository

↓

Search Engine (Hybrid)

- Keyword Search
- Semantic Vector Search
- AI Ranking Layer

---

# State Management

SearchState includes:

- idle
- loading
- results
- error

Core Data:

- query
- filters
- results
- suggestions
- recentSearches

---

# Search Scope

Search must include:

- Courses
- Lessons
- AI Tutor responses
- AI Chat history
- Notes
- Bookmarks
- Quiz questions
- Mock exams

---

# Search Modes

1. Keyword Search
2. Semantic Search
3. AI Answer Search
4. Learning Path Search

---

# Ranking System

Results ranked by:

- relevance score
- user progress
- recent activity
- difficulty match
- AI prediction of usefulness

---

# AI Integration

AI enhances search by:

- rewriting queries
- expanding intent
- suggesting next actions
- summarizing results

---

# Filters

- course type
- difficulty level
- jurisdiction
- content type
- progress status

---

# Navigation Rules

Search results must route to:

- Course Details
- Lesson Player
- Quiz Engine
- AI Tutor
- Notes Viewer

---

# Offline Behaviour

- cached search results available
- no semantic AI search offline
- keyword search only offline

---

# API Contracts

GET /search?q=

POST /search/suggest

GET /search/history

---

# Analytics Events

search_query

search_result_click

search_no_results

search_filter_used

---

# UX Rules

- results must appear instantly
- suggestions must guide user intent
- avoid empty states where possible

---

# UI Composition Rules

Search UI must include:

- search bar
- filters panel
- categorized results
- recent searches
- AI suggestions

---

# Error Handling

- fallback to cached results
- show helpful suggestions on no results

---

# Performance

- search response <300ms target
- debounce input queries

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- voice input (future-ready)
- screen reader result navigation
- keyboard search navigation

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Search ranking logic

Filter system

Query parsing

Widget Tests:

Search UI

Results rendering

Filter interaction

Integration Tests:

Full search flow

AI ranking integration

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating search features:

- always include semantic + keyword hybrid search
- always rank using learning relevance
- always support cross-module results
- never return raw unranked results to UI